27 ONE-TIME APPROPRIATIONS
28 Sec. 401. (1) From the funds appropriated in part 1 for
29 accelerated resentencing hearings, the state appellate defender
SCS S06110'26 (S-1) ku92es

19
1 office may hire up to 4.0 limited-term employees to support and
2 accelerate the agency's juvenile lifer resentencing program, as
3 described in section 313.
4 (2) The unexpended appropriations in part 1 for accelerated
5 resentencing hearings are designated as a work project
6 appropriation. Any unencumbered or unallotted funds shall not lapse
7 at the end of the fiscal year and shall be available for
8 expenditure for the project under this section until the project
9 has been completed. The following is in compliance with section
10 451a of the management and budget act, 1984 PA 431, MCL 18.1451a:
11 (a) The purpose of the project is to supplement and accelerate
12 juvenile lifer resentencing hearings as required by law.
13 (b) The project will be accomplished by utilizing state
14 resources and contracts.
15 (c) The total estimated completion cost of the project is
16 $2,000,000.00.
17 (d) The tentative completion date for the work project is
18 September 30, 2030.
